&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/15/01/Mech%20Paper%202_Image-Q6.PNG&quot; style=&quot;height:348px; width:227px&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;there4; for the solution to be unique,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Rank of the augmented matrix = number of variables&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\rm = 3\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\rm ∴ b ≠ 5\)&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;and&amp;nbsp;a can be any value.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\begin{array}{l} x.\frac{{dT}}{{dx}} + T = {e^x}\\ \therefore \frac{{dT}}{{dx}} + \frac{T}{x} = \frac{{{e^x}}}{x} \end{array}\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Comparing with:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\begin{array}{l}
\frac{{dy}}{{dx}} + P\left( x \right).y = Q\left( x \right)\\
I.F = {e^{\smallint P\left( x \right)dx}}\\
\left( {I.F} \right)y = \smallint \left( {I.F} \right)Q\left( x \right)dx
\end{array}\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Integrating factor =&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\({e^{\mathop \smallint \nolimits \frac{1}{x}.dx}} = {e^{\ln x}} = x\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\begin{array}{l} \therefore {\rm{}}T.\left( {IF} \right) = \mathop \smallint \nolimits \left( {I.F} \right).Q.dx + C\\ \therefore {\rm{}}Tx = \mathop \smallint \nolimits x.\frac{{{e^x}}}{x}.dx + C\\ \therefore Tx = {e^x} + C \end{array}\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Initial condition, T(0) = 1&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;there4; C = - 1&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\begin{array}{l} \therefore T = \frac{{{e^x}}}{x} - \frac{1}{x}\\ \therefore T\left( 2 \right) = \frac{{{e^2}}}{2} - \frac{1}{2} = 3.19 \end{array}\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As per Cauchy Integral formula,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\({f^n}\left( {{z_0}} \right) = \frac{{n!}}{{2\pi i}}\mathop \oint \nolimits \frac{{f\left( z \right)}}{{{{\left( {z - {z_0}} \right)}^{n + 1}}}}.dz\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Put z&lt;sub&gt;0&lt;/sub&gt; = -1 and n = 3, and f(z) = e&lt;sup&gt;2z&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\begin{array}{l} \therefore f&#039;&#039;&#039;\left( {{z_0}} \right) = 8{e^{ - 2}}\\ \therefore 8{e^{ - 2}} = \frac{{3!}}{{2\pi i}}\mathop \oint \nolimits \frac{{{e^{2z}}}}{{{{\left( {z + 1} \right)}^4}}}.dz\\ \therefore \mathop \oint \nolimits \frac{{{e^{2z}}}}{{{{\left( {z + 1} \right)}^4}}}.dz = \frac{8}{3}\pi i{e^{ - 2}} \end{array}\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Concept&lt;/u&gt;:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Simpson 3/8&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt; rule is stated as:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\mathop \smallint \limits_a^b y \cdot dx = \frac{{3h}}{8}\left[ {\left( {{y_0} + {y_n}} \right) + 2\left( {{y_3} + {y_6} +  \ldots } \right) + 3\left( {{y_1} + {y_2} + {y_4} \ldots } \right)} \right]\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Where:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(h = \frac{{b - a}}{n}\)&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;and &amp;#39;n&amp;#39; must be multiple at &amp;lsquo;3&amp;rsquo;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Calculation&lt;/u&gt;:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Given:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(I = \mathop \smallint \limits_1^2 \frac{1}{{{x^2}}} \cdot dx\)&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;and n = 3&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\therefore ~h = \frac{{2 - 1}}{3} = \frac{1}{3}\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

