&lt;p&gt;Now by cauchy&amp;rsquo;s integral formula,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(f({z_o}) = {1 \over {2\pi i}}\int\limits_c {{{f(z)} \over {z - {z_o}}}} dz\)&lt;/span&gt;&amp;rarr;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\int\limits_c {{{f(z)} \over {z - {z_o}}}} dz\)&lt;/span&gt;=&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(2\pi i\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(f({z_o})\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Take f(z) = cos&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 20.7999992370605px;&quot;&gt;&amp;pi;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 20.7999992370605px;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;z, z&lt;sub&gt;o &lt;/sub&gt;= 1,we have&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\int\limits_{\left| z \right| = 3} {{{\cos \pi z} \over {z - 1}}} dz = 2\pi if(1) = 2\pi icos\pi = - 2\pi i\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Concept:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Analytic function f(z) = u (x, y) + iv (x, y)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If f(z) = u + iv is analytic function, then u and v must satisfy&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Cauchy-Riemann (C-R) equation&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\frac{{\partial u}}{{dx}} = \frac{{dv}}{{dy}}\;and~\frac{{du}}{{dy}} = - \frac{{\partial v}}{{dx}}\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Calculation:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\rm f(z) = u+i v = e^x (\cos ky+i \sin ky)\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(u(x,y)=e^x \cos ky ~~ and ~~\ v(x,y)=e^x\sin ky\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\rm u_x = e^x \cos ky ~;~u_y = -ke^x \sin ky\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\rm v_x = e^x \sin ky ~;~v_y = ke^x cos ky\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For analytic function Cauchy Riemann equations has to be satisfied&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So &lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\rm u_x = v_y \ and \ u_y = -v_x\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(u_x=v_y \Rightarrow \rm e^x \cos ky = ke^x \cos ky \)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(u_y=-v_x \Rightarrow -ke^x \sin ky = -e^x \sin ky\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;so k = 1&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Using Stoke&amp;rsquo;s theorem:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\oint\limits_L {F.dL = \int\!\!\!\int\limits_S {(\nabla \times F).dS} }\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\nabla \times F = - {x^2}{u_z}\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

