&lt;p&gt;But in a circle unlike a line there is no start and end but if we put 1 object O&lt;sub&gt;k&lt;/sub&gt; at a specific place we can arrange all other objects in (n &amp;ndash; 1)! ways with respect to O&lt;sub&gt;k&lt;/sub&gt;. Note that when objects around O&lt;sub&gt;k&lt;/sub&gt; will be arranged in all possible ways O&lt;sub&gt;k&lt;/sub&gt; will also get arranged around them in all possible ways.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Now to arrange 4 boys around the table:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/16/10/Images1st.PNG&quot; style=&quot;height:192px; width:202px&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(ways = \left( {4 - 1} \right)! = 3! = 6\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Now to arrange 4 girls so that no two girls are adjacent to each other&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/16/10/Images2nd.PNG&quot; style=&quot;height:197px; width:203px&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We have 4 distinguishable positions:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hence total number of arrangements:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\left( {4 - 1} \right)! \times 4! = 3! \times 4! = 144\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;np = 4 and npq = 3&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;thus q = (3/4) and p = (1-q) = (1/4)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;mode is an integer such that np+p &amp;gt; x &amp;gt; np-q&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; 4 +(1/4) &amp;gt; x &amp;gt;4-(3/4)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; (13/4)&amp;lt;x&amp;lt;(17/4)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;3.25&amp;lt;x&amp;lt;4.25&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; x=4&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Concept&lt;/u&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;According to Newton-Raphson Method&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\({X_{n + 1}} = {X_n} - \frac{{f\left( {{X_n}} \right)}}{{f&#039;\left( {{X_n}} \right)}}\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Calculation&lt;/u&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Given that, f(x) =&amp;nbsp;x - cos(x)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;f&amp;#39;(x) = 1 +&amp;nbsp;sin(x)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Intial value, x&lt;sub&gt;0&amp;nbsp;&lt;/sub&gt;= 1&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\({x_1} = {x_0} - \frac{{f\left( {{x_0}} \right)}}{{f&#039;\left( {{x_0}} \right)}}\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\( = {x_0} - \frac{{{x_0} - \cos {x_0}}}{{1 + \sin {x_0}}}\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\( = 1 - \frac{{1 - \cos 1}}{{1 + \sin 1}} = 0.752\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Common Mistake&lt;/u&gt;:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here the initial value is given in &lt;strong&gt;radians. &lt;/strong&gt;So,&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;while calculating the trigonometric functions, it must be converted into &lt;strong&gt;degrees&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;matrix &amp;lsquo;A&amp;rsquo; &amp;rArr; &lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(f(x) = a_0 + a_1x + a_2x^2 + ………. + a_{n-1}x^{n-1} + a_nx^n\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;if 2 &amp;times; 2 matrix then characteristic equation &amp;nbsp;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(⇒ aλ^2 + bλ + c = 0\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(⇒ |A| = λ_1. λ_2. = \frac {c}{a}\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;where&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(a_o=c\;\;;a_n=a_2=a\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;if 3 &amp;times; 3 matrix &amp;rarr; then characteristic equation &lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\( ⇒ aλ^3 + bλ^2 + cλ + d = 0\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(⇒ |A| = λ_1. λ_2. λ_3 =- \frac {d}{a} \)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;where&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(a_o=d\;\;;a_n=a_3=a\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\therefore\)&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;For&amp;nbsp;n &amp;times; n matrix,&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\left| A \right| = {\lambda _1}.{\lambda _2}.{\lambda _3} \ldots .{\lambda _n} = {\left( { - 1} \right)^n}\frac{{{a_0}}}{{{a_n}}}\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;here &lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\rm (z=2)\)&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is a&amp;nbsp;pole&amp;nbsp;of order 4 which lies inside the&amp;nbsp;region &lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\rm |z|=3\)&lt;/span&gt; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\rm |z|=3\)&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is a&amp;nbsp;circle of radius 3 with center at (0,0)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;then by Cauchy&amp;#39;s Integral Formula we have&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\rm \mathop \smallint \limits_c \frac{{{z^2}{e^{2z}}}}{{{{\left( {z - 2} \right)}^4}}}dz = \frac{{2\pi i}}{{3!}}f&#039;&#039;&#039;\left( z \right) - - - - - - - - - \left( 1 \right)\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\begin{array}{l} f\left( z \right) = {z^2}{e^{2z}}\\ f&#039;\left( z \right) = 2{z^2}{e^{2z}} + 2z{e^{2z}} = 2{e^{2z}}\left( {{z^2} + z} \right)\\ f&#039;&#039;\left( z \right) = 4\left( {{z^2} + z} \right){e^{2z}} + 2{e^{2z}}\left( {2z + 1} \right) = 2{e^{2z}}\left( {2{z^2} + 4z + 1} \right)\\ f&#039;&#039;&#039;\left( z \right) = 4{e^{2z}}\left( {2{z^2} + 4z + 1} \right) + 2{e^{2z}}\left( {4z + 4} \right)\\ = 4{e^{2z}}\left( {2{z^2} + 4z + 1 + 2z + 2} \right) = 4{e^{2z}}\left( {2{z^2} + 6z + 3} \right)\\ f&#039;&#039;&#039;\left( 2 \right) = 4{e^4}\left( {8 + 12 + 3} \right) = 92{e^4} \end{array}\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;from equation (1), we get&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\mathop \smallint \limits_c \frac{{{z^2}{e^{2z}}}}{{{{\left( {z - 2} \right)}^4}}}dz = \frac{{2\pi i}}{{3!}}*92{e^4} = \frac{{92\pi i}}{3}{e^4}\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;poles :&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\rm z^2 + 4 = 0 ⇒ z = ± 2i\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;region in consideration&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\rm → |z-i|=2\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\rm |x+i(y-1)|= 2 \)&lt;/span&gt;is a circle of radius &lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\rm 2\)&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;having center at&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\rm (0,1)\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/15/09/GATE_Math_SubjectTest_2_Images-Q25.PNG&quot; style=&quot;height:182px; width:184px&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;pole &lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\rm z =2i \)&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is inside the region&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;so Res.&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\begin{array}{*{20}{c}} {f\left( z \right)}\\ {z = 2i} \end{array} = \mathop {\lim }\limits_{z = 2i} \left( {z - 2i} \right)\frac{{sin\pi {z^2} + cos\pi {z^2}}}{{\left( {z - 2i} \right)\left( {z + 2i} \right)}}\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(= \frac{{{\rm{sin}}\left( { - 4\pi } \right) + {\rm{cos}}\left( { - 4\pi } \right)}}{{4i}} = \frac{{0 + 1}}{{4i}} = \frac{1}{{4i}}\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;then by Cauchy Residue Theorem we have&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\mathop \smallint \limits_c \frac{{sin\pi {z^2} + cos\pi {z^2}}}{{{z^3} + 4}} = 2\pi i\left( {\frac{1}{{4i}}} \right) = \frac{\pi }{2}\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

en.value:
&lt;p&gt;Let &lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\rm A\)&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;be a&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\rm n × n\)&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;orthogonal matrix and&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\rm X\  is \ a \ n × 1\)&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;matrix, then&amp;nbsp;for system&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\rm P : AX = B\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\rm  Q : Z = A^TB\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Where &lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\rm Z \ is \ a \ n × 1\)&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;matrix which is identical to&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\rm X\)&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;Matrix. Then&lt;/p&gt;

sol.value:
&lt;p&gt;Given that &lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\rm AX = B \)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;given Matrix &lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\rm A\)&lt;/span&gt; is an Orthogonal Matrix hence&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\rm A.A^T=I\Rightarrow A^T=A^{-1}\)&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Since &lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\rm Z\)&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is identical to &lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\rm X\)&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;we can have&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\rm AZ=B\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\rm A^{-1}(AZ)=A^{-1}B\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\rm (IZ)=A^{-1}B\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\rm \therefore (Z)=A^{-1}B=A^T.B\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;there4; Both &lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\rm P \ and\  Q\)&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;have same solution&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Given &lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\({\rm{A}} = \left[ {\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}
1&amp;amp;1&amp;amp;0\\
0&amp;amp;1&amp;amp;0\\
1&amp;amp;0&amp;amp;1
\end{array}} \right]\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Trace (A) = 1 + 1 + 1 = 3&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\begin{array}{l}
\left| {\rm{A}} \right|{\rm{}} = {\rm{}}1{\rm{}}\left( {1{\rm{}}-{\rm{}}0} \right){\rm{}}-{\rm{}}1{\rm{}}\left( 0 \right){\rm{}} = {\rm{}}1\\
{{\rm{M}}_{11}}{\rm{}} + {{\rm{M}}_{22}}{\rm{}} + {\rm{}}{{\rm{M}}_{33}}{\rm{}} = {\rm{}}1{\rm{}} + {\rm{}}1{\rm{}} + {\rm{}}1{\rm{}} = {\rm{}}3
\end{array}\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;there4; Characteristic of given matrix is,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\begin{array}{l}
 - {{\rm{\lambda }}^3} + {\rm{trace}}\left( {\rm{A}} \right){{\rm{\lambda }}^2} - \left( {{{\rm{M}}_{11}} + {{\rm{M}}_{22}} + {{\rm{M}}_{33}}} \right){\rm{\lambda }} + \left| {\rm{A}} \right| = 0\\
 - {{\rm{\lambda }}^3} + 3{{\rm{\lambda }}^2} - 3{\rm{\lambda }} + 1 = 0 \Rightarrow {{\rm{\lambda }}^3} - 3{{\rm{\lambda }}^2} + 3{\rm{\lambda }} - 1 = 0
\end{array}\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;From the Cauley Hamilton theorem, we have&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\begin{array}{l}
{{\rm{A}}^3} - 3{{\rm{A}}^2} + 3{\rm{A}} - {\rm{I}} = 0\\
{{\rm{A}}^3} = 3{{\rm{A}}^2} - 3{\rm{A}} + {\rm{I}}\\
{{\rm{A}}^4} = 3{{\rm{A}}^3} - 3{{\rm{A}}^2} + {\rm{A}}\\
\therefore {{\rm{A}}^4} - 3{{\rm{A}}^3} =  - 3{{\rm{A}}^2} + {\rm{A}}
\end{array}\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
